        <div type="letter">
            <div type="text">
                <opener>
                    <placeName>Down</placeName>
                    <date>Wednesday | July 31<hi rend="superscript">st</hi>. 44</date>
                    <salute>Dear Jos</salute>
                </opener>
                <div type="transcription">
                     
<p>I write merely to acknowledge the order for <hi rend="superscript">£</hi>48"4<hi rend="superscript">s</hi>"8<hi rend="superscript">d</hi> &amp; to thank you.—</p>
<p>It sounds very dangerous the 5 000£ being deposited without any security, but if you like to keep this note as security, I here engage to give to you full indemnification.<ref target="#foot.f1"/></p>
<p>Ever yours | Charles R. Darwin</p> 
                </div>
            </div>

            
            
        </div>

        

        

        <div type="footnotes">
            <note xml:id="foot.f1">The £5000 referred to was part of a £20,000 sum made over to Robert Waring Darwin by CD and <ref target="../nameregs/nameregs_1218.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">Emma Darwin</ref>; the £20,000 formed the basis of a mortgage loan to Edward Herbert, second earl of Powis (R. W. Darwin’s Investment book (Down House MS), pp. 57, 70). See <hi rend="italic">Correspondence</hi> vol. 3, <ref target="./DCP-LETT-766.xml" resp="#mjhawkins">letter to Josiah Wedgwood III and E. A. Darwin, 25 July 1844</ref>. The other transaction has not been identified.</note>
        </div>        
            
